                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d422">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">865D.01/230: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Italy</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Phillips</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-28T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >December 28, 1936—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>194. Your 550, December 24, 1 p.m. We are inclined to feel it would be better not
                    to stress the proposed change in status of our representation at Addis Ababa by
                    making any formal announcement at this time. Engert will probably be about to
                    depart on leave towards the end of February and the change in status will become
                    known at that time in a routine manner.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Moore</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
